5- FloodFilling ¶

In [319]:
# Using the Thresholding image
DilatedFloodFilled = dilate.copy()

# Mask used to flood filling.
# The size needs to be 2 pixels larger than the image.
h, w = Dilation.shape[:2]
FloodFilling_Mask = np.zeros((h+2, w+2), np.uint8)

# Floodfill from point (0, 0)
cv2.floodFill(DilatedFloodFilled, FloodFilling_Mask, (0,0), 255)

# Invert floodfilled image
DilatedFloodFilled_Inverted = cv2.bitwise_not(DilatedFloodFilled)

# Combine the two images to get the foreground.
dilate_out = Dilation | DilatedFloodFilled_Inverted

def ImageContouring(img,imgcontour):
    contours, hierarchy = cv2.findContours(img,cv2.RETR_EXTERNAL, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_NONE)
    plate_img=[]
    
    for cnt in contours:
        
        area = cv2.contourArea(cnt)
        print(area)

        
        if  area > 1400 :
            min_rect = cv2.minAreaRect(cnt)
            print(min_rect)
            x,y,w,h = cv2.boundingRect(cnt)
            print(x,y,w,h)
            return x,y,w,h

7- Optical Character Recognition (OCR) ¶

In [333]:
def OCR(x,y,w,h,org_img):
    print(x,y,w,h)
    plate_img = org_img[y:y+h,x:x+w]
    plate_im = Image.fromarray(plate_img)

    text = tess.image_to_string(plate_img, lang='eng')
    plt.imshow(plate_img,'gray')
    return text

In [343]:
def OCR_Image(text,org_img):
    
    text=OCR(x,y,w,h,test)
    font = cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX
    bottomLeftCornerOfText = (x,y-10)
    fontScale = 1
    fontColor = (240,68,83)
    lineType = 2

    img = cv2.rectangle(org_img,(x,y),(x+w,y+h),(255,255,255),4)
    cv2.putText(org_img,text,
        bottomLeftCornerOfText, 
        font, 
        fontScale,
        fontColor,
        lineType)
    plt.imshow(img, 'gray')
